dsDescriptionValue.value:
The present dataset contains supporting data for: Heidlmayr K, Doré-Mazars K, Aparicio X, Isel F (2016). Multiple Language Use Influences Oculomotor Task Performance: Neurophysiological Evidence of a Shared Substrate between Language and Motor Control. PLoS ONE. DOI: 10.1371/journal.pone.0165029.

The dataset contains electroencephalographical data from 19 bilingual and 20 monolingual participants recorded during an Antisaccade task. Preprocessed EEG, mean amplitudes for time windows of interest, ERSP (event-related spectral perturbation; time-frequency analysis) and DCM (dynamic causal modelling) data, as well as behavioral and language background data are provided. See README.txt for further details.
